# Production Environment Variables Template
# Copy this file to your hosting platform's environment variables settings
# DO NOT commit actual values to git!

# ============================================
# REQUIRED - Supabase Configuration
# ============================================
# Get from: Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key-here

# ============================================
# REQUIRED - Email Configuration (Resend)
# ============================================
# Get from: https://resend.com/api-keys
RESEND_API_KEY=re_your_api_key_here

# ============================================
# REQUIRED - Application URLs
# ============================================
# Set to your production domain (NO trailing slash)
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://your-domain.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://your-domain.com

# ============================================
# OPTIONAL - AWS S3 (if using S3 for storage)
# ============================================
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your-aws-access-key
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your-aws-secret-key
# AWS_REGION=us-east-1
# AWS_S3_BUCKET=your-bucket-name

# ============================================
# Deployment Platform Specific Instructions
# ============================================

## Vercel:
## 1. Go to: Project Settings → Environment Variables
## 2. Add each variable above with production values
## 3. Make sure to select "Production" environment
## 4. Redeploy after adding variables

## Netlify:
## 1. Go to: Site Settings → Environment Variables
## 2. Add each variable with production values
## 3. Trigger new deploy

## Railway/Render:
## 1. Go to environment variables section
## 2. Add all variables
## 3. Service will auto-redeploy

# ============================================
# Verification Checklist
# ============================================
# After setting environment variables:
# [ ] NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL is set
# [ ] NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY is set
# [ ] SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY is set
# [ ] RESEND_API_KEY is set and starts with 're_'
# [ ] NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL points to production domain (HTTPS)
